Zapatero Changed Constitution After ECB Letter, Periodico Says

-- B y   A n g e l i n e   B e n o i t
-- 
2011-10-04T08:55:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/zapatero-changed-constitution-after-ecb-letter-periodico-says.html
 Spanish Prime Minister Jose Luis Rodriguez Zapatero decided to enshrine fiscal discipline in the
constitution in August in line with demands in a letter from
European Central Bank President  Jean-Claude Trichet ,  El
Periodico  said, citing an unidentified government spokesman.  Zapatero received a letter calling for guarantees and a
clear commitment to stabilize  Spain ’s finances, the spokesman
said, according to the daily newspaper’s website.  No one from Zapatero’s office was immediately available for
comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Angeline Benoit in Madrid at 
 abenoit4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at 
